---
layout: base.njk
title: Experience Levels
description: Find the right yoga difficulty level for your practice
---

<section class="page-header">
  <h1>Experience Levels</h1>
  <p>Find the right class for your yoga journey</p>
</section>

<section class="guide-section-container">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="guide-section-wrapper">
      <div class="guide-section-intro">
        <h2>Finding Your Level</h2>
        <p>Yoga is accessible to everyone, regardless of experience or physical ability. Understanding the different experience levels can help you choose classes that will challenge you appropriately and support your growth.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="guide-selector">
        <div class="guide-selector-buttons">
          {% for level in site.difficultyLevels %}
            <button class="guide-selector-btn" data-target="{{ level | slug }}">
              <span>{{ level }}</span>
            </button>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="guide-content-container">
        {% for level in site.difficultyLevels %}
          <div class="guide-content-box" id="{{ level | slug }}-content">
            <h2>{{ level }}</h2>
            <div class="level-content">
              {% if level == "Beginner" %}
                <div class="level-description">
                  <p>Perfect for those just starting their yoga journey. These classes focus on basic postures, proper alignment, and building a foundation for your practice.</p>

                  <div class="level-details">
                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>What to Expect</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Simple, foundational poses</li>
                        <li>Detailed instruction and alignment cues</li>
                        <li>Slower pace with time to explore each pose</li>
                        <li>Frequent modifications and prop suggestions</li>
                        <li>Focus on proper breathing techniques</li>
                        <li>Shorter holding times</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>Recommended For</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Those new to yoga practice</li>
                        <li>People returning after a long break</li>
                        <li>Those working with limitations or injuries</li>
                        <li>Anyone wanting to refine their foundation</li>
                        <li>Those looking to learn proper technique</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>Benefits of Starting Here</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Builds a strong foundation for your practice</li>
                        <li>Prevents injury by learning proper alignment</li>
                        <li>Develops body awareness and mindfulness</li>
                        <li>Builds confidence before advancing</li>
                        <li>Creates sustainable practice habits</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              {% elif level == "Intermediate" %}
                <div class="level-description">
                  <p>For practitioners with some yoga experience. These classes introduce more complex poses, transitions, and longer holds to deepen your practice.</p>

                  <div class="level-details">
                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>What to Expect</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Faster-paced flows and sequences</li>
                        <li>More challenging pose variations</li>
                        <li>Less detailed instruction (assumes basic knowledge)</li>
                        <li>Longer sequences between breaks</li>
                        <li>Introduction to inversions and arm balances</li>
                        <li>Deeper exploration of breath techniques</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>Recommended For</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Regular practitioners (6+ months experience)</li>
                        <li>Those comfortable with basic poses and alignment</li>
                        <li>Students wanting to deepen their practice</li>
                        <li>Those with good body awareness</li>
                        <li>Practitioners looking for more challenge</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>Benefits of This Level</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Builds upon your foundation</li>
                        <li>Increases strength and flexibility</li>
                        <li>Deepens your understanding of yoga philosophy</li>
                        <li>Enhances mind-body connection</li>
                        <li>Develops more advanced breathing techniques</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              {% elif level == "Advanced" %}
                <div class="level-description">
                  <p>Challenging practices for experienced yogis. These classes include advanced postures, complex sequences, and require greater strength and flexibility.</p>

                  <div class="level-details">
                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>What to Expect</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Complex arm balances and inversions</li>
                        <li>Deep backbends and forward folds</li>
                        <li>Challenging transitions between poses</li>
                        <li>Minimal instruction (assumes significant experience)</li>
                        <li>Advanced pranayama techniques</li>
                        <li>Longer holds in challenging positions</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>Recommended For</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Dedicated practitioners (2+ years experience)</li>
                        <li>Those with strong body awareness</li>
                        <li>Students with established home practice</li>
                        <li>Those with significant strength and flexibility</li>
                        <li>Practitioners looking to refine advanced poses</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>Benefits of This Level</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Pushes physical and mental boundaries</li>
                        <li>Refines advanced techniques</li>
                        <li>Deepens meditation aspects of practice</li>
                        <li>Develops advanced breathing control</li>
                        <li>Offers new challenges to experienced practitioners</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              {% else %}
                <div class="level-description">
                  <p>Suitable for practitioners of all experience levels. These classes offer modifications for beginners and challenges for more experienced students.</p>

                  <div class="level-details">
                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>What to Expect</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Options for different skill levels</li>
                        <li>Accessible base poses with additional variations</li>
                        <li>Balanced pace with modifications</li>
                        <li>Clear cues for both beginners and advanced students</li>
                        <li>Community-oriented atmosphere</li>
                        <li>Focus on personal progress</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>Recommended For</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Mixed-level groups</li>
                        <li>Families practicing together</li>
                        <li>Studios with diverse students</li>
                        <li>Those who prefer variety in their practice</li>
                        <li>Anyone wanting a balanced approach</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="level-detail-item">
                      <h3>Benefits of This Level</h3>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Accessible to everyone</li>
                        <li>Encourages personal adaptations</li>
                        <li>Builds community across experience levels</li>
                        <li>Teaches how to modify for your needs</li>
                        <li>Provides a well-rounded practice</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              {% endif %}
              <a href="/difficulty/{{ level | slug }}/" class="btn secondary-btn">View {{ level }} Videos</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    // Get all selector buttons and content boxes
    const selectorButtons = document.querySelectorAll('.guide-selector-btn');
    const contentBoxes = document.querySelectorAll('.guide-content-box');

    // Set first content box as active by default
    if (contentBoxes.length > 0) {
      contentBoxes[0].classList.add('active');
      selectorButtons[0].classList.add('active');
    }

    // Add click event to each button
    selectorButtons.forEach(button => {
      button.addEventListener('click', function() {
        const targetId = this.getAttribute('data-target');
        const targetContent = document.getElementById(`${targetId}-content`);

        // Remove active class from all buttons and content boxes
        selectorButtons.forEach(btn => btn.classList.remove('active'));
        contentBoxes.forEach(box => box.classList.remove('active'));

        // Add active class to clicked button and its content
        this.classList.add('active');
        targetContent.classList.add('active');
      });
    });
  });
</script>

